## Cultural Hooks

1. **Мала академія наук України (МАН)** — Founded 1947 as the first pupils' science society in Kyiv; in 2018 received UNESCO Science Education Centre Category II status (first and only Ukrainian educational structure with this status, decided unanimously at the 39th UNESCO General Conference). Also in 2018, МАН received Copernicus Academy status, giving Ukrainian school researchers access to data from 29 European satellites. Source: uk.wikipedia.org/wiki/Мала_академія_наук_України. The Law of Ukraine "On Scientific and Scientific-Technical Activity" (2015) defines МАН as a network for "forming the intellectual capital of the nation and raising the future scientific generation." This is a powerful, decolonised frame — Ukrainian youth science infrastructure recognised internationally.

2. **Вернадський Володимир Іванович** — First president of the Ukrainian Academy of Sciences (1918); founder of geochemistry, biogeochemistry, and the concept of the noosphere. His method was radically systematic: he believed that organising knowledge — seeing connections across disciplines — is itself a scientific act. This idea of системне мислення underpins the plan's cultural hook for the "Topic Selection and Scientific Approach" section. Source: uk.wikipedia.org/wiki/Вернадський_Володимир_Іванович. **Decolonisation note**: Вернадський is often listed primarily as a Russian/Soviet scientist. He was Ukrainian — founding president of Українська академія наук, and his intellectual legacy belongs to Ukrainian science.

---

## Common Learner Errors

1. **"Я вірю" calque** → Correct: "На нашу думку" / "Як свідчать факти" / "Варто зазначити". Why: English-speaking learners transfer "I believe/I think" directly, producing subjective-sounding academic prose. Ukrainian academic register uses impersonal or plural constructions.

2. **"дослід" vs "дослідження" false friends** → дослід = a single experiment (laboratory/empirical test); дослідження = research, a study (the broader process). Why: English "study" and "experiment" are sometimes used interchangeably in casual speech; Ukrainian distinguishes them lexically and using wrong form signals poor register control.

3. **English quotation marks "" instead of Ukrainian «»** → Correct: Ukrainian typographic convention uses «» for all quotation in formal/academic text. Why: most learners type on English-layout keyboards where `"` is the default; the error is common in student-generated Ukrainian text and signals lack of orthographic awareness at B2 level.

4. **Passive voice under-use / calque from English active voice** → Ukrainian academic writing frequently uses безособові конструкції (Вважається, що...; Було встановлено, що...; Дослідження показують...). Learners often default to English-style active subject + verb, producing unnatural academic Ukrainian.

