## Notes for Content Writing

- **Register consistency**: All prose must be in neutral-academic style (нейтральний register as marked in plan). No colloquial turns. Every section should model the register it teaches.
- **Безособові конструкції** as both content and example: when teaching "Вважається, що...", "Варто зазначити...", the module text itself should use these forms — learners absorb through exposure.
- **Word target allocation**: 4000 words across 6 sections (500/700/900/700/800/400). The largest section (Section 3: Academic Integrity, 900 words) needs careful structure — split into: typology of sources → academic integrity principles → citation mechanics → paraphrase vs. quotation.
- **False friend дослід/дослідження**: Treat with a concrete example pair, not just definition.
- **Vернадський hook**: Frame as Ukrainian scientist first. Use his principle of системне мислення as the entry point for the "choose your topic" section — a student who sees connections across domains will find better research questions.
- **МАН hook**: Opens the Introduction section as the cultural anchor — this is the institution where Ukrainian students do exactly what this module teaches. Grounds the module in a real Ukrainian context.
- **Passive constructions**: Section 5 (Writing the Draft) is the natural place to integrate пасивний стан examples — "у роботі було розглянуто", "встановлено, що", "можна вважати" — as B2 grammar review items in context.
- **Ukrainian quotation marks «»**: Model correct usage throughout the module text itself, not just in the explanatory passage.
- **Plan-проспект structure**: Introduce with a clear visual or enumerated model (вступ → основна частина → висновки) mirroring the Grade 11 Voron description. Learners at B2 have likely seen реферат structure in Ukrainian schools; this module extends it into research context.

